abstract: The company, after resisting requests from European officials, agreed to turn over information it collected over unsecured wireless networks.
snippet: The company, after resisting requests from European officials, agreed to turn over information it collected over unsecured wireless networks.
lead_paragraph: Google is bowing to the demands of three European governments and says it will begin surrendering the data it improperly collected over unsecured wireless networks.

headline.main: Google to Give Governments Street View Data

abstract: Deal-wise along Madison Avenue, it is not quite back to the frenzied buy-up days before the financial crisis, but two acquisitions announced on Thursday, by Google and Hearst, indicate that things may be picking up, particularly in the digital realm.

abstract: A subsidiary, General Motors Ventures, plans to invest in start-up companies in fields including renewable fuels, information and entertainment systems, and advanced materials.
snippet: A subsidiary, General Motors Ventures, plans to invest in start-up companies in fields including renewable fuels, information and entertainment systems, and advanced materials.
lead_paragraph: General Motors said Friday that it was committing $100 million to form its own venture capital firm as it seeks new technologies that can provide an advantage over competitors, The New York Times’s Nick Bunkley reports from Detroit.

headline.main: G.M. Plans a Technology Venture Firm
